            "Experimental Setting. A summary of datasets and models for evaluations can be found in Table 2. By default, we employ CNN and the non-i.i.d. FEMNIST dataset (partition parameter α=0.5𝛼0.5\\alpha=0.5), as the non-i.i.d. setting closely captures real-world scenarios. We utilize FedAVG in our experiments.\nBy default, we use 10 clients for FL training, corresponding to real-world FL applications where the number of clients is typically less than 10, especially in ToB scenarios. We also increase the number of clients to 20 in the real-world experiment, where we utilize edge devices from the Theta network (Theta Network., 2023) (Exp 7).\nEvaluations for anomaly detection are conducted on a server with 8 NVIDIA A100-SXM4-80GB GPUs, and evaluations for ZKP are conducted on Amazon AWS with an m5a.4xlarge instance with 16 CPU cores and 32 GB memory. We implement the ZKP system in Circom (Contributors, 2022)."
